==English==
===Pronunciation===
* ''[[RP]]:''
** {{IPA|/fəʊlɪˈeɪʃn/}}

===Noun===
'''foliation'''
# The process of [[form]]ing into a [[leaf]] or leaves.
# The manner in which the young leaves are disposed within the [[bud]].
# The act of beating a [[metal]] into a thin [[plate]], leaf, [[foil]], or [[lamina]].
# The act of coating with an [[amalgam]] of [[tin]] foil and [[quicksilver]], as in making [[looking-glass]]es.
# The [[enrichment]] of an opening by means of foils, arranged in [[trefoil]]s, [[quatrefoil]]s, etc.; also, one of the [[ornament]]s.
# The property, possessed by some [[crystalline]] [[rock]]s, of dividing into [[plate]]s or [[slab]]s, which is due to the [[cleavage]] structure of one of the [[constituent]]s, as [[mica]] or [[hornblende]]. It may sometimes include [[slaty]] structure or cleavage, though the latter is usually independent of any [[mineral]] constituent, and [[transverse]] to the [[bedding]], it having been produced by [[pressure]].

